OL,3,CDriving test rules to change in bid to
OL,4,Ccut backlog and stop bots booking slots
OL,6,FDefence driving examiners (DDEs) `
OL,7,Fcivil servants at the MoD who usually
OL,8,Ftest service personnel ` will conduct
OL,9,Ftests one day a week for 12 months.
OL,10,FThe MoD will charge the DVSA #100,000
OL,11,Ffor using the DDEs.
OL,13,FThe DfT said deploying military
OL,14,Fsupport to public test centres will
OL,15,F"benefit both parties" as it will keep
OL,16,Ftheir "skills sharp" while also
OL,17,Ftackling the backlog.
OL,19,FThey will be focused primarily on car
OL,20,Fdriving tests but can carry out tests
OL,21,Ffor bus and lorry drivers if needed.
